Class MapDBHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
      • MapDBHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ContentHandler, DTDHandler, EntityResolver, ErrorHandler

    public class MapDBHandler
extends DefaultHandler
    Parses OSM XML files using an XML SAX parser. Used to construct the graph of roads for pathfinding, under some constraints. See OSM documentation on the highway tag, the way XML element, the node XML element, and the java SAX parser tutorial.
    Author:
    Alan Yao

    • Field Detail

      • ALLOWED_HIGHWAY_TYPES

        private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_HIGHWAY_TYPES
        Only allow for non-service roads; this prevents going on pedestrian streets as much as possible. Note that in Berkeley, many of the campus roads are tagged as motor vehicle roads, but in practice we walk all over them with such impunity that we forget cars can actually drive on them.
